-- TABLE-Asia-Pacific ECM volumes drop in first half
-- By Denny Thomas
-- Sun Jun 29, 2014 09:00PM EDT
-- None



HONG KONG, June 30 (Reuters) - Asia-Pacific equity capital market (ECM) volumes fell marginally in the first half of 2014 to $87.5 billion from $89.3 billion from a year ago. Total fees generated by all ECM issuance by Asia-Pacific companies shot up 64.2 percent to $2.31 billion, the data showed. [ID:nL4N0P71PT]

